Interesting anecdotes about wolves from story I read yesterday; 

Sometimes a female gives birth to four wolf-pups, of which all but one die - the pup that is left drinks all the milk meant for all four and gets very large and strong.  This is how a "lone wolf" begins its life.

Some wolves use the trick to lie on the ground/snow and roll around/make "whining" noises like a dog playing - they use this to bait in a horse or other animal, that comes to sniff them/check them - the wolf jumps on its neck immediately.

The wolf "warfare" is very complex - the story told of a pack of wolves sending one smaller one to attract the dogs in a farm - as they chased him, other wolves ambushed them in forest, meanwhile "alpha" who was a "lone wolf" snuck in farm and killed and took lots of sheep.Clever
